<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1905-03-16T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1905-03-16T00:00:00-05:00" n="109" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d109">
                        <head><hi rend="italic">Minister <persName type="from">Townsend</persName>
                                to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>.</hi></head>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">American Legation</hi>,<lb/><hi rend="italic">Brussels</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1905-03-16"><hi rend="italic">March 16,
                                1905</hi></date>.</dateline>
                            <seg rendition="#left">No. 253.]</seg></opener>
                        <p><hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: I have the honor to acknowledge the
                            receipt of Department’s cable of yesterday’s date. * * *</p>
                        <p>In conformity with instructions, I have signed the protocol of the
                            International Maritime Conference held at Brussels, February 25 last. *
                            * *</p>
                        <p>I have, etc.,</p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Lawrence
                            Townsend.</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>